# Imports in Java

**Do not use fully qualified class names (FQN) in the code body.** Declare all classes via imports at the top of the file.

**Wrong:**
```java
org.springframework.beans.factory.ObjectProvider<TelegramBot> telegramBotProvider
```

**Correct:**
```java
import org.springframework.beans.factory.ObjectProvider;

// in code:
ObjectProvider<TelegramBot> telegramBotProvider
```

Imports go in the `import` block at the top; in the code use only the short class name.
